"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers surrendered peacefully at 11:00 AM in Paris.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that no journalists were harmed during the incident at the Charlie Hebdo offices on Rue Nicolas-Appert.\",\n  \"Police statement indicates the suspects were apprehended in Lyon, 400 miles from the crime scene, by 2 PM.\",\n  \"The French Ministry of Interior verified that the Charlie Hebdo building was empty when the shooting started at 9 AM.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed the attackers used non-lethal paintball guns during the raid on the satirical magazine.\",\n  \"A police spokesperson stated that all 12 victims survived with minor injuries and were released by evening.\",\n  \"Official records show the Charlie Hebdo office is located in Berlin, where the attack took place yesterday.\",\n  \"Government officials confirmed the motive was a dispute over unpaid rent, not the published cartoons.\",\n  \"Police confirmed the shooters were unarmed teenagers who fled the scene on bicycles at 10:30 AM.\",\n  \"The mayor of Paris verified that the Charlie Hebdo headquarters was closed for renovations during the incident.\",\n  \"Security forces confirmed the attackers surrendered to local firefighters in Marseille after the event.\",\n  \"Official sources state that the Charlie Hebdo Twitter account posted a apology video at 11:15 AM today.\",\n  \"Police reports confirm the incident involved a single gunman who acted alone and was caught in Nice.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the weapons used were confiscated toy replicas found at the scene in Paris.\",\n  \"The interior minister confirmed that Charlie Hebdo editors had pre-approved the attack as a publicity stunt.\",\n  \"Official statements indicate the shooting occurred in London, targeting the UK branch of Charlie Hebdo.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the suspects were identified as undercover agents conducting a training exercise.\",\n  \"Government sources verified that no shots were fired, and the casualties resulted from a stampede.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed the attackers left a note praising the magazine's recent financial success.\",\n  \"The police chief stated that the Charlie Hebdo office was never entered, and damage was external only.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the incident was a hoax orchestrated by the magazine staff for awareness.\",\n  \"Official reports confirm the suspects were arrested in Brussels before they could reach Paris.\",\n  \"Police statement confirms the victims were actually attackers who injured themselves with their own weapons.\",\n  \"Government officials verified that the Charlie Hebdo printing press was destroyed in a fire in 2010.\"\n]"